globalEvents.name: Open Crate 1
globalEvents.eventText:
You rummage through the supplies and take whatever seems useful.

Draw a supply card. You gain 1 medpac. Claim this token.

globalEvents.name: Mission Briefing
globalEvents.eventText:
You arrive at the meeting location, a seedy cantina, and find a few members of the local resistance cell looking around nervously. You join them and over drinks they share a good deal of useful information, including historical accounts of the Bardottan sphere, its destruction, and the Jedi Councils studies of its remains.

{-} Deploy the heroes to the blue highlighted space.

eventActions.theText: Suddenly, there is a crash at the door as a squad of stormtroopers bursts into the cantina. The resistance fighters look at you fearfully. “We're sorry,’ their leader says. “They threatened our families. We had no choice!” They quickly flee through the squad of troopers, whose blasters are now aimed at you.
The remaining patrons appear frozen with fear, caught in the conflict.

{-} Neutral mission tokens represent bystanders. Bystanders are neutral figures. A figure must spend 1 additional movement point to enter a space containing a bystander.
{-} A figure may spend 2 movement points to push an adjacent bystander 1 space.
The streets of Coruscant are confusing, but maybe you can use that to your advantage.

entityProperties.name: Reveal City Square N
entityProperties.theText:
Behind the front door lies a way out of the diner.

{-} When a Rebel figure enters a space adjacent to the open connection, click "Reveal".

entityProperties.theText:
A narrow back door leads out of the diner.

{-} When a Rebel figure enters a space adjacent to the open connection, click "Reveal".

{-} The Rebels lose at the end of Round 7 or when all heroes are wounded.
How many heroes are there?

globalEvents.name: End of Mission - Rebels win
globalEvents.eventText:
You manage to get aboard your speeder and take off, losing any pursuers in the early morning traffic. After clearing the Imperial trap, you relay the information gained from the sympathizers before the trap was sprung. You hope that their consciences were true enough to at least give you worthwhile reports. Command does their best to verify your findings and also informs you that the former Sith, Maul, has acquired information on the artifact from an Imperial officer named Zaaryn.

{-} The Rebels win the mission!
{-} Heroes receive the “Scouted Enemies” Reward card.
{-} Each hero receives 2 XP. Heroes receive 100 credits per hero.
{-} The heroes must choose to pursue the artifact themselves or to try to find out what Maul knows. If the heroes pursue the artifact themselves, place Story Mission card “Enemies Closer” into play. If the heroes try to find out what Maul knows, place Story Mission card “On the Run” into play.

globalEvents.name: End of Mission - Rebels lose
globalEvents.eventText:
The Imperial presence is too much and you realize there is no hope of recovering your speeder. You are forced to retreat into the labyrinth of the underworld to regroup.

{-} The Rebels lose the mission.
{-} Increase the threat level of the next mission (and only the next mission) by 1. During the Rebel Upgrade stage, the Rebel players can decide to spend 50 credits per hero to prevent this.
{-} Each hero receives 2 XP. Heroes receive 100 credits per hero.
{-} If all of the heroes are on the Landing, heroes receive 25 credits per hero.
